Bolaji Tunji, spokesman to late former Oyo Governor, Abiola Ajimobi, has said that his burial would strictly be a family affair. The aide explained that this was in line with COVID-19 safety protocol. Tunji made the disclosure to newsmen in Ibadan on Friday. “With deep sadness and deep regret, but in total submission to the will of the Almighty Allah, we announce the transition of His Excellency, Sen. Ishaq Abiola Adeyemi Ajimobi. “The sad event occurred on Thursday after a brief illness. He was aged 70 years. Funeral details will be anounced later,” he said. Tunji added that arrangement on the funeral ceremony would be communicated later.